## Configuration Options

Users can now configure the tool via:
- **Environment variables** for seamless CI/CD integration
- **CLI flags** for command-line usage
- **Python API** for programmatic use

### Example Usage (Environment Variables)
```bash
# Agent Platform with ADC
export GOOGLE_GENAI_USE_ENTERPRISE="true"
export GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT="your-project-id"
export GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION="us-central1"

# Agent Platform with API Key
export GOOGLE_GENAI_USE_ENTERPRISE="true"
export GOOGLE_API_KEY="your-api-key"
```

### Example Usage (CLI)
```bash
gst translate -i subtitle.srt -l French --use-enterprise --cloud-project "your-project-id" --request-type "shared"
```

### Example Usage (Python API)
```python
import gemini_srt_translator as gst

gst.use_enterprise = True
gst.cloud_project = "your-project-id"
gst.cloud_location = "us-central1"
gst.request_type = "shared"
```

## Technical Highlights

- ✅ Intelligent mode detection based on provided credentials
- ✅ Support for both "shared" and "dedicated" request types in enterprise mode
- ✅ Service tier validation skipped for enterprise mode
- ✅ Token validation skipped for enterprise mode (handled by platform)
- ✅ Graceful fallback handling for missing credentials
- ✅ Updated model listing logic for enterprise models
- ✅ Enhanced error handling and retry logic (including 429 rate limit errors)